The @friendsfromnewyork holiday party was TOO fun! I came up playing downtown Manhattan when it was the center of the universe, 4-5 nights a week and it was rap, rnb, reggae, 80’s, house and disco every night. I’m not a “back in the days” type but it’s very nice to celebrate/relive those times once in a while! And I love Djing w @stretcharmstrong who not only was such a huge influence on me as a wee tween but also can play a Phil Collins song like no one else in the world!

If I was to play the last DJ set of my life, I’d start it with this song and end it with this song. This is the song that made me know I wanted to play dance music and showed me the kind of emotion dance music was capable of generating. I love it. The best song ever. 
(It was playing at Trader Joe’s cc @chocolatinaruiz )
Merry Xmas from freezing cold, totally deserted and romantic NYC. 🎄
2022 wrapped. Thanks to everyone who listened to and supported my music in all of its very different forms. I appreciate it so much!

Not to be negative but I kinda hate live streaming and everything it represents but whatever I played a set at the @razorntape store on their super nice set up and you can watch or listen to it now. I played a lot of my favorite 80’s and early 90’s records and drank wine. It’s on YouTube! Link in stories.
New year, same me!
Happy heavenly birthday Jemz. We miss you.
Another Wednesday, another DanceDanceDance at @lebainnyc and somehow this party just keeps getting better. Tonight it’s me and @dedelovelace playing. Come thru!
RIP Dino. Hope wherever you are the dj is playing “Souvenirs.”

Tomorrow night is @houseofyesnyc ‘s 7th anniversary. I’m forever grateful to HOY for trusting me and giving me the opportunity to play open til close every month. As I get older, dj sets become more and more personal. I think of my life, friends that have passed away and all the memories I’ve accumulated over the years, especially in night clubs. It can be sad, it can be joyous and always therapeutic. I can’t really describe it. HOY posted my 6 hours plus set from last month and it’s pretty all over the place. But I guess that’s life. 

Listen if you’d like. Link in stories and I’ll be back tomorrow night for another round! 💕

social_posts.post_text:
In 2010 @lebainnyc somehow decided to let @enterthelloyd @blujemz and me take over Saturday nights. The club had just opened and NYC was undergoing a nightlife makeover. Thank god. For three insane years we had the time of our lives in that place. We played all the music we wanted to hear in clubs and people actually liked it! It was like a dream. Lots of babies in that crowd - future friends and family. 
@enterthelloyd and I are gonna bring back Night People this Friday in remembrance of our best friend James. 
10-4 at Le Bain (which is still the greatest by the way!) 
📸 @kennyrodz

So I made an Essential Mix. That feels crazy to type. Growing up in NYC I will be honest, the essential mix was not something that was on my radar, but as the world got smaller and so many mixes became available online, I deep dived into the series and repeatedly listened to some of my favorites like Derrick Carter, 2manydjs and Daft Punk’s mix. 
So I feel really honored to be able to contribute myself. 
I thought a lot about what music I would include and decided to skip over the obvious disco or 90’s house references. I reflected more on the last 10-15 years of my career as those years have been so crucial to where I’ve ended up now. I thought about songs I’ve been playing throughout  the 2010’s up til now and what’s held up really well. It’s a very genre non-specific mix. That’s how I like my dance music! 

You can listen live this Friday (tomorrow) from midnight - 2am GMT 21/01/23 @bbcradio1 (7pm NYC time) or listen later on @BBCSounds
 #R1Dance

Whoo hoo!

Ok I swear I’m gonna leave you guys alone after this post.
I have a new EP called Still Searchin’ out today! Just some raw trax 4 u. Really happy w it. And super big thanks to @hannahsdarkroom for the photo from Black Flamingo where,  incidentally, I am playing tomorrow night open to close! 
Also I did a @djmagofficial selections article today talking about some of the cool stuff I like right now. Including songs from @venicearms @idjut_boys @perelmusic @erolalkan @josh_caffe @laurenflax @posthumanmusic @andrea.tempo and more. Link in stories. 
Ok have a great weekend everyone!

He pronounced my name right! I didn’t get to listen live cause disco naps are important. But the archive is up now. I put the link in my stories and also swipe for the full track list if you’re interested. 💕

New York’s house and disco evangelist... a DJs, DJ who we think has earned the term ‘Legend’ 💯

A devoted collector, explorer and connoisseur of music, coming from hip-hop roots, https://www.instagram.com/eliescobarnyc/ is a NYC instituation in his own right. Climbing to relevancy by spinning in some of the most culturally relevant New York clubs over the last two decades, his productions across the who's who of electronic music labels have cemented his legacy as a one of the greats…

There’s not many who knows the scene quite like Eli, so we’re pretty honoured to have curate a line-up for one of our March @houseofyesnyc dates ✨

I used to play every Saturday night at this place called Parlay on Avenue A. The dj booth was about 8 feet above the floor and only accessible by a ladder. I used to bring 5 crates of records and somehow get them up this rinky dink ladder without killing myself and then spend the entire night djing while totally hidden from view while everyone danced below me. 
Silo is the exact opposite of that club. 
And tons of fun. I loved it! Thnx everyone who came out!

I finally got to play Printworks in London (right before they close) and it was super fun! Now here’s a little tip for you up and coming DJ’s: if you never “let” yourself get too popular, you’ll always get put in the smaller, darker, more ravey rooms and it’s always better! So dj with your head down, try not to smile and definitely don’t accept the applause at the end of your sets! It’ll all work out for the best, trust me.

Eli Escobar returns for his 9th full length LP. While his last few projects found him exploring downtempo beats, EBM and ambient influences, this latest offering of Eli’s studio craftsmanship marks a return to the sound of his early releases like Up All Night and Happiness. Warm samples expertly woven into classic drum machine rhythms and searing synth lines, The Beach Album takes listeners on a journey through golden era hip hop beats, feel-good NY-styled house grooves into sweaty techno bangers. Similar to Eli’s DJ sets, the 16 track long player has something for everyone. Created during the uncertainty of the pandemic when as Eli put it, „It didn’t feel like the right time to release dance music,“ The Beach album celebrates the return of NY nightlife and optimism for the future.

We asked our friend and NYC nightlife veteran @eliescobarnyc to contribute a mix for the series, and he delivered!🔥

With over two decades of electronic music eminence, Eli Escobar has confirmed his place amongst dance music greats. With an unparalleled record collection of handpicked gems and curveball productions, Escobar guides revellers through the heartbeat of music, from the past to the future. 
 
Always looking forward and keeping step with evolving generational tastes, Escobar has redefined his sound in recent years. As an acquainted DJ & Producer, the dance music veteran cut his teeth into the epicentre of 1990’s New York City hedonism and set the foundations for an admirable career. Releasing music on influential labels such as Phonica, Razor n Tape, Defected’s ‘Classic’ and his very own label imprint Night People, only gives a snapshot into the depth of his discovery. 
 
Spanning over more than 20 years, the influence and presence of Eli Escobar is undeniable in every corner of dance music. As a selector he has appeared on a variety of influential platforms including BBC Radio 1 Essential Mix, Resident Advisor's Exchange Podcast, Boiler Room, Mixmag ‘The Lab’ and The Lot Radio, only to name a few. Likewise transporting his sound to dancefloors across the world with residencies at House of Yes, Le Bain, Battlehymn and beyond. 
 
Globally respected and recognised as a forward thinking producer, Escobar’s output steps beyond conventional dance music with remix work for the likes of Lana Del Rey, M.I.A., Honey Dijon, Cakes Da Killa and many more. Now heading into 2023 Eli looks to stay true to his musical progression.

Hit the link in bio to listen, and be sure to catch @eliescobarnyc when he’s in your city!

While I have grown very bored with the self promotional side of Instagram, I have no trouble expressing gratitude. So on that note I want to really thank everyone who came out to @goodroombk on Saturday! I actually get really nervous about these all night sets in the age of ticket sales and anxious bookers (I’m about to become one myself) and all the different venues and choices people have. It’s a lot of pressure! So I so appreciate the support and enthusiasm you guys show me weekend after weekend. 😍 This particular night at Good Room was so fun and I played so many songs without drums. I’m like the Alchemist of dance music. Ok I’m rambling. Bye!

Well there’s officially a new drink ticket in my pockets. 
Where do I start here - this past weekend was literally a dream come true. My friend Rafael @cafemogadornyc  and I met at Manhattan East JHS in East Harlem in the fucking late 80s! We teamed up with his cousins to make this place real and doing it with people I’ve literally known for 3 decades or more is so meaningful. 
We started a little Pinterest mood board 2 years ago and the club feels like it actually came to life. Thanks to the genius @arenas8625 ! It’s surreal! And I’m so grateful to be working with people I’ve known for so so long on this project. Like @queenadine who started doing lights at @lebainnyc when she was 18 and her and her dad @caramelproductionnyc gave us the most insane sound. And @chelleave who made our logo exactly perfectly. @motheragave the best GM ever! @the_real_ericdlc and @ralvarezartcom my dream door team! I’m so excited for this place to just exist now! And go to my stories for a thank you present for making opening weekend so amazing. We’ll re-open again this Thursday!
So wild to be in @interviewmag . Thank you @eloiseie - teenage Eli dreamed of this moment!
